WEBVTT

00:02.160 --> 00:03.446
STEFAN: Previously on
The Vampire Diaries...

00:03.600 --> 00:05.125
I'm moving to Dallas
and I'm leaving today.

00:05.320 --> 00:07.243
- I've hired a nurse to come with me.
- What?

00:07.440 --> 00:09.090
- Do you have a better idea?
- Me.

00:09.240 --> 00:11.447
I will fix this. Stefan, I promise you.

00:11.640 --> 00:14.371
DAMON: I have a way to take down Rayna,
in a pile of bricks called the Armory.

00:14.600 --> 00:16.523
BONNIE: The Armory
is a black hole of lies.

00:17.280 --> 00:18.327
(c; ROWLS)

00:19.280 --> 00:20.327
(GRUNTS)

00:20.640 --> 00:21.766
No.

00:22.000 --> 00:23.764
You're not supposed to die for me, Bon.

00:24.000 --> 00:25.047
Neither's my brother.

00:25.280 --> 00:27.647
Which is why I have to
take myself out of the equation.

00:27.960 --> 00:30.122
You'll never have to worry about me again.

00:31.040 --> 00:33.042
Welcome to New Orleans.

00:33.280 --> 00:34.850
Freya, Stefan needs a favor.

00:35.040 --> 00:36.883
FREYA: A mystical vampire Huntress

00:37.120 --> 00:39.122
-stabbed you with her magic sword.
-(G RU NTS)

00:39.280 --> 00:40.327
Stefan.

00:40.560 --> 00:44.042
FREYA: Klaus killed her,
but surprise, surprise.

00:44.280 --> 00:45.327
STEFAN: She regenerates.

00:45.520 --> 00:46.806
FREYA: And won't rest until you're dead.

00:47.000 --> 00:48.286
<i>STEFAN: No matter how far I run,</i>

00:48.520 --> 00:50.807
this wound acts as a beacon,
drawing her to me.

00:51.000 --> 00:54.527
Well, I can't cure the wound,
but this paste will mask its signal.

01:03.360 --> 01:04.407
(BIRDS CHIRPING)

02:22.480 --> 02:23.561
What do you want?

02:23.960 --> 02:25.644
Just lookin' for a bite.

02:25.840 --> 02:28.286
Oh, God. You're a vampire.

02:28.600 --> 02:29.840
And you're lunch.

02:31.280 --> 02:32.770
-(GUNSHOTS)
-(GRUNTS)

02:35.120 --> 02:36.451
- Shouldn't he be turning all gray?
-(SHAWN GROANS)

02:37.760 --> 02:39.285
PENNY: All the other ones turned gray.

02:39.480 --> 02:41.289
Unless, of course... You missed?

02:41.480 --> 02:43.005
How many vampires have I killed
in the last few days?

02:43.200 --> 02:45.282
A lot. But who knows
how many you would have killed

02:45.480 --> 02:47.084
if you hadn't missed a third of the time.

02:47.280 --> 02:49.965
He's got a thick jacket on.
I can't see exactly where his heart is.

02:50.280 --> 02:51.930
Outerwear? That's your excuse?

02:52.120 --> 02:54.202
-(c:ocl<s GUN)
%GUNSHOT)

02:56.960 --> 02:58.849
You gonna stand there and brag all day

02:59.040 --> 03:00.724
or are you gonna help me
load him into the truck?

03:00.920 --> 03:02.046
We got to get him out of here, before--

03:02.280 --> 03:03.930
KRYSTAL: Julian's other vampires
get suspicious?

03:05.320 --> 03:06.765
Too late.

03:09.800 --> 03:11.165
Touch it and die.

03:14.040 --> 03:15.963
Actually, why don't you die anyway.

03:16.160 --> 03:17.400
(RAPID GUNSHOTS)

03:25.200 --> 03:27.407
- RAYNA: You saved our lives.
- Yes, I did.

03:27.840 --> 03:29.285
Which means you owe me one.

03:30.680 --> 03:33.445
Have you ever heard of a vampire
named Stefan Salvatore?

03:41.720 --> 03:42.767
(SIGHS)

03:43.520 --> 03:46.171
You mind just paying attention
to the road a little bit more?

03:46.360 --> 03:48.488
You know, I could, but then I might miss

03:48.680 --> 03:50.842
the world's largest ball of yarn
coming up on the left.

03:52.040 --> 03:53.326
And there it goes.

03:54.360 --> 03:55.805
Not quite sure what I was expecting.

03:56.040 --> 03:58.611
Well, that was the last of Freya's herbs.

03:58.840 --> 03:59.887
Which means it's only a matter of time

04:00.080 --> 04:01.650
before they wear off,
and Rayna can track me.

04:01.880 --> 04:03.609
- Good thing we're on our way to get more.
- Are we?

04:03.840 --> 04:05.330
Because it sure feels
like we're on our way

04:05.520 --> 04:07.010
to the world's largest waste of time.

04:07.200 --> 04:09.202
We have to take back roads
to avoid being spotted.

04:12.000 --> 04:14.765
You've only been running
a few days, Stefan.

04:14.960 --> 04:17.406
- Think of it like it's an adventure.
-(SCOFFS)

04:18.000 --> 04:19.490
I don't want an adventure.

04:19.680 --> 04:21.808
I just want to get these herbs
and have a nice quiet

04:22.000 --> 04:23.843
home-cooked meal with my girlfriend.

04:24.040 --> 04:26.441
Then do what? Pay bills?

04:26.640 --> 04:28.005
Talk about your day?

04:28.240 --> 04:29.287
Ugh.

04:29.480 --> 04:30.527
(SIGHS)

04:30.840 --> 04:33.241
Wait, you don't actually enjoy this,
do you?

04:33.520 --> 04:36.205
Hmm. There's a certain constant
in the lack of constants.

04:36.640 --> 04:40.042
Once you accept it, it's invigorating.

04:43.160 --> 04:44.491
We're here.

04:46.400 --> 04:48.129
What is this place?

04:49.240 --> 04:51.049
Oh, well, according to Freya,

04:52.080 --> 04:53.923
all the herbs witches use are stored here.

04:54.200 --> 04:55.725
Just in case something happens to them.

04:55.920 --> 04:57.684
- All of them?
- Yeah.

04:58.120 --> 05:01.727
(SIGHS) Well, I hope you know
what this particular herb looks like...

05:02.880 --> 05:04.291
STEFAN; And Why is that?

05:05.080 --> 05:07.924
Because witches are very fond
of their herbs.

05:09.440 --> 05:10.487
(RINGING)

05:12.200 --> 05:13.406
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

05:14.400 --> 05:16.448
-(SLAMS PHONE)
- Oh, good. You're up.

05:16.800 --> 05:18.245
How's Bonica Magica?

05:18.440 --> 05:20.442
Not great, but...

05:21.800 --> 05:23.564
Good enough to make sure
you never call me that again.

05:23.800 --> 05:24.961
Ooh!

05:25.440 --> 05:26.680
-(CHUCKLES)
- Someone's cheery.

05:26.880 --> 05:28.041
- Well, I'm a man with a plan.
-(CLINKS)

05:28.320 --> 05:29.924
- Which is?
- A secret.

05:30.280 --> 05:32.009
Does it have to do
with killing Rayna, the Huntress?

05:32.320 --> 05:33.560
I'll never tell.

05:33.840 --> 05:35.968
But, yes.

05:36.160 --> 05:37.571
- Good. How can I help?
- You can't.

05:37.760 --> 05:38.921
This is the Damon only show.

05:39.120 --> 05:40.770
It's Damon, versus Rayna.

05:40.960 --> 05:42.644
Because that won't get you
right back in hell.

05:42.840 --> 05:44.126
You don't even know how to kill her.

05:44.360 --> 05:45.407
-(SCOFFS)
-(CELL PHONE RINGING)

05:47.960 --> 05:50.327
- But you know who might?
- Don't even think about it.

05:50.520 --> 05:52.329
-(DISCONNECTS)
- Enzo's been calling me nonstop.

05:52.520 --> 05:54.409
- Probably to apologize for yesterday.
-(CELL PHONE RINGING)

05:54.640 --> 05:56.768
I bet if I go back to the Armory,
I can find out more info.

05:57.080 --> 05:58.809
- What the hell?
- Well, look around, Bonnie.

05:59.040 --> 06:01.247
I'm not here
for the filmy hospital pudding.

06:01.480 --> 06:02.925
You almost died in that place.

06:03.120 --> 06:05.043
And I'll never let that happen again.

06:05.400 --> 06:07.528
Promise me you will stay out of this, Bon.

06:07.840 --> 06:09.683
No one needs to get hurt for me anymore.

06:10.960 --> 06:12.769
I can handle Rayna.

06:17.480 --> 06:18.720
Here's where we stand.

06:19.000 --> 06:20.161
I've killed five of your friends

06:20.400 --> 06:22.687
because they couldn't tell me
where Stefan Salvatore was.

06:23.120 --> 06:24.326
I sure hope you can.

06:24.520 --> 06:26.363
You two, watch and learn.

06:26.560 --> 06:28.801
The key is to treat them
like you would a wild animal.

06:29.000 --> 06:31.765
Respecting the danger,
but recognizing that they're beneath you.

06:31.960 --> 06:33.689
And that they serve a purpose.

06:34.400 --> 06:37.882
For example,
this one will provide information.

06:39.440 --> 06:42.444
Tell me everything you know
about Stefan Salvatore

06:42.640 --> 06:44.847
or I'll send you to hell for eternity.

06:45.040 --> 06:47.168
DAMON: Barking up the wrong vampire there,
sister.

06:47.360 --> 06:48.407
(RAYNA GASPS)

06:49.320 --> 06:52.085
Stefan's anti-social. Not many friends.

06:52.280 --> 06:53.486
Actually no friends at all.

06:53.720 --> 06:55.722
But I hear he has a very handsome
and charming brother,

06:55.920 --> 06:57.001
you might want to talk to him.

06:57.200 --> 06:58.531
Yeah, a stupid brother.

06:59.280 --> 07:00.884
Seems foolish of you to come back here.

07:01.080 --> 07:02.161
DAMON; Ikn0W. Right?

07:02.400 --> 07:05.529
To be honest, I'm not that brave.

07:06.680 --> 07:10.446
I did have a shockingly effective ally
tell me that you were here.

07:10.640 --> 07:11.687
Hmm.

07:11.880 --> 07:12.961
%GUNSHOT)
-(GRUNTS)

07:13.200 --> 07:14.247
(GASPS)

07:14.560 --> 07:16.005
(GRUNTS)

07:16.480 --> 07:18.130
(GROANS)

07:22.520 --> 07:25.364
- What the hell did you do?
- It's okay. Damon's a...

07:25.560 --> 07:27.881
Aw, you almost said friend. How sweet.

07:28.080 --> 07:29.684
His brother is a friend.

07:29.920 --> 07:31.763
And that's the only reason
I'm helping him.

07:32.080 --> 07:33.525
And the world yawned.

07:33.800 --> 07:34.847
Get rid of this thing.

07:35.760 --> 07:36.921
Anything else?

07:37.720 --> 07:38.881
Yeah.

07:39.080 --> 07:40.764
You know where I can get a buzz saw?

07:44.840 --> 07:46.171
(BIRDS CHIRPING)

07:51.600 --> 07:52.647
(WHISTLING)

08:20.120 --> 08:21.167
(GROANS)

08:21.560 --> 08:23.085
Here we go.

08:29.320 --> 08:30.970
(BONES CRACKING)

08:32.120 --> 08:33.201
(BREATHES DEEPLY)

08:43.640 --> 08:44.971
DAMON: They're my girlfriend's.

08:45.160 --> 08:48.209
I mean, given the fact
that you two look exactly alike,

08:48.400 --> 08:49.526
you should be able to fit in them.

08:49.760 --> 08:52.127
RAYNA: What's next?
It puts the lotion in the basket?

08:52.320 --> 08:55.085
It wouldn't have to
if it just stayed dead.

08:55.560 --> 08:56.641
(SIGHS)

08:57.120 --> 08:58.804
I'm in a bit of a pickle here, Ray.

08:59.280 --> 09:01.009
I've got big plans.

09:01.440 --> 09:02.680
You buy a time-share?

09:03.120 --> 09:04.167
DAMON: Kind of, actually.

09:04.320 --> 09:07.449
But I can't go on vacation,
until I do something about you.

09:07.640 --> 09:10.007
See, I can't relax and sip mai tais

09:10.200 --> 09:12.089
while you're out hunting my brother,

09:12.320 --> 09:15.767
and every time I kill you,
you just phoenix back to life.

09:16.520 --> 09:18.807
(SIGHS)
It's a dill.

09:19.000 --> 09:21.367
RAYNA: Well, why don't you just let me
kill your brother,

09:21.560 --> 09:23.642
then you can do
whatever the hell you want?

09:23.840 --> 09:24.887
DAMON: Tempting. Truly.

09:25.200 --> 09:26.725
But, I kind of owe him.
(SIGHS)

09:27.360 --> 09:29.203
Family, am I right?

09:29.520 --> 09:31.170
That's why you and I
have to put our heads together

09:31.360 --> 09:32.691
and come up with a plan B.

09:32.920 --> 09:36.402
You want me to go against my very nature
because he's your family?

09:36.840 --> 09:38.001
Pretty much.

09:39.880 --> 09:40.927
Funny thing is,

09:41.520 --> 09:43.648
family is the very reason
this is my nature.

09:45.040 --> 09:48.408
My father envisioned
a world without vampires.

09:49.200 --> 09:52.682
I will not rest
until I see his vision through.

09:55.440 --> 09:56.487
(SIGHS)

09:57.000 --> 09:58.889
So, what do you propose we do?

09:59.080 --> 10:01.208
Rub each one on your wound
and hope for the best?

10:01.400 --> 10:03.641
No, you're a witch.
Why have you never heard of this?

10:05.360 --> 10:06.486
VALERIE: It is strange.

10:06.680 --> 10:09.081
Botanically, I am very well-versed.

10:09.400 --> 10:11.084
There's wolfsbane.

10:11.720 --> 10:13.882
Vervain. Senna.

10:14.360 --> 10:15.566
Witch hazel.

10:15.840 --> 10:18.320
- And this fun little guy.
- Mmm.

10:18.920 --> 10:19.967
That one I know.

10:20.520 --> 10:22.045
The witchy hallucinogen?

10:22.240 --> 10:24.766
The one borderline recreational herb?

10:25.240 --> 10:27.925
Stefan. I misjudged you.

10:29.560 --> 10:31.050
You actually do have fun.

10:32.000 --> 10:33.161
I did it once.

10:33.640 --> 10:35.881
- What was her name?
- Really? There has to be a her?

10:36.080 --> 10:39.084
With someone like you?
There's always a bad influence.

10:41.560 --> 10:44.291
Well, her name was Rebekah.

10:45.120 --> 10:46.565
Let's just say, she was a lot to handle.

10:46.760 --> 10:48.967
VALERIE: (CHUCKLES)
Of course she was.

10:49.160 --> 10:51.288
And that's why she's not in the picture.

10:51.760 --> 10:55.082
So you prefer small-town girls
who want to settle down.

10:55.280 --> 10:57.248
-(SIGHS)
- Who are easy to handle.

10:57.440 --> 11:00.842
I don't think anyone has ever called
Caroline Forbes easy to handle.

11:02.240 --> 11:05.130
And as thrilling
as this therapy session is,

11:06.160 --> 11:07.650
I think I found it.

11:07.840 --> 11:09.251
Or where it used to be.

11:09.480 --> 11:11.482
Lovely. A dead end.

11:11.760 --> 11:12.807
(AIR HISSING)

11:13.040 --> 11:14.485
What is that?

11:16.840 --> 11:18.410
Night, night.

11:19.880 --> 11:20.927
%GAsPs)
%THUDS)

11:29.160 --> 11:30.571
(DOOR WHIRRS AND BEEPS)

11:31.800 --> 11:34.485
- You actually came. I'm shocked.
-(DOOR CLOSES)

11:35.240 --> 11:36.480
So did it grow back, or--

11:36.680 --> 11:38.444
No, actually. I had to reattach it.

11:38.640 --> 11:40.130
But thank you for your concern.

11:40.320 --> 11:41.481
Less concern. More curiosity.

11:41.720 --> 11:43.165
Well, at least you're thinking of me.

11:43.480 --> 11:45.448
- I take it you received my messages.
- I did.

11:45.680 --> 11:48.206
And I'm not stupid enough to think
that your apologies were anything

11:48.400 --> 11:50.243
other than a tactic to get me here.

11:50.480 --> 11:51.766
But here I am.

11:51.960 --> 11:56.204
Fair warning,
if you try to disable my magic again,

11:56.440 --> 11:58.807
-you'll wish I had only cut off your hand.
-(SIGHS)

11:59.360 --> 12:02.125
I see Damon's obscenity
is rubbing off on you.

12:02.360 --> 12:03.646
It's quite pathetic, really.

12:03.840 --> 12:07.162
You know, you following him around
like some high school groupie.

12:07.360 --> 12:11.763
Hmm. I forgot you two used to be friends
and now you have none.

12:12.000 --> 12:13.729
- You think you're friends?
-(DOOR WHIRRS AND OPENS)

12:14.040 --> 12:15.485
Lorenzo.

12:17.360 --> 12:18.407
(DOOR BEEPS)

12:20.320 --> 12:22.049
You must be Bonnie Bennett.

12:22.520 --> 12:24.887
I'm Alex St. John. Welcome to the Armory.

12:26.800 --> 12:28.882
I'm sorry for Enzo's behavior yesterday.

12:29.080 --> 12:30.570
He wasn't following proper protocol.

12:30.760 --> 12:32.171
I asked him to call you back here.

12:32.360 --> 12:34.328
We might have gotten off
on the wrong foot.

12:34.560 --> 12:35.686
The wrong foot? Or?

12:35.880 --> 12:37.166
Not funny.

12:37.400 --> 12:39.721
I dunno. It's kind of funny.
(CHUCKLES)

12:40.760 --> 12:42.285
Rayna Cruz is a common enemy.

12:42.480 --> 12:44.084
We should be working together
to fight her.

12:44.320 --> 12:46.209
But you don't want to fight her,

12:46.400 --> 12:47.765
you want her captured.

12:47.960 --> 12:50.725
So I think you know a lot more
than you're letting on.

12:51.040 --> 12:52.849
Makes it hard for me to trust you.

12:53.360 --> 12:54.407
Fair.

12:56.880 --> 12:58.041
Why don't you come with me?

13:03.720 --> 13:07.725
This room contains everything
the Armory has gathered on Rayna Cruz.

13:08.080 --> 13:12.290
A list of victims. Her lineage.
The spell used to create her.

13:12.920 --> 13:16.686
And most importantly,
the Shamans that gave their lives for her.

13:17.160 --> 13:18.924
The Eight Everlastings.

13:22.760 --> 13:25.525
You mean Two Everlastings.

13:25.720 --> 13:27.882
The other six look pretty lasted.

13:28.200 --> 13:30.646
ALEX: There should be
three preserved corpses...

13:35.160 --> 13:36.571
We lost another one?

13:36.920 --> 13:38.570
Did you know about this?
Why wasn't I told?

13:38.760 --> 13:40.444
It must have just happened.

13:41.440 --> 13:42.680
Dammit.

13:44.080 --> 13:45.127
(SIGHS)

13:45.280 --> 13:47.806
I take it from her subtle shift
in attitude that's a bad thing?

13:48.000 --> 13:50.367
Every time Rayna dies,
one of the bodies decays.

13:50.600 --> 13:52.090
We've lost quite a few this past week.

13:52.280 --> 13:54.282
And if we lose all of them,
Rayna dies for good.

13:57.800 --> 13:58.961
So...

13:59.640 --> 14:02.246
Hunting vampires is your identity.

14:02.480 --> 14:05.643
Your fundamental, "This is who I am,"

14:06.680 --> 14:07.920
in a nutshell.

14:09.600 --> 14:11.523
You ever wonder
if there was a way to change that?

14:11.800 --> 14:14.087
No. I don't. Because there's not.

14:14.280 --> 14:15.327
I used to think that.

14:15.480 --> 14:16.527
Look, I'm selfish.

14:16.720 --> 14:20.202
Narcissistic.
Prone to unnecessary bouts of violence.

14:20.480 --> 14:22.209
Tell me again
why I shouldn't be killing you?

14:22.400 --> 14:24.050
Because I changed.

14:24.240 --> 14:26.607
I mean, temporarily, as it were,
but it happened.

14:26.840 --> 14:27.887
It just took the right person.

14:28.040 --> 14:29.087
Maybe you haven't found the right person.

14:29.240 --> 14:32.084
I don't need a vampire matchmaker.
But thanks.

14:32.280 --> 14:33.850
<i>DAMON: Well, I mean,
have you ever even tried?</i>

14:34.040 --> 14:37.169
Has there ever been a Mr. Hunter, huh?

14:39.880 --> 14:40.927
Oh...

14:41.280 --> 14:42.486
There has been.

14:43.480 --> 14:44.527
(CHUCKUNG)

14:45.520 --> 14:46.567
(CELL PHONE BUZZING)

14:47.080 --> 14:48.127
I see.

14:53.160 --> 14:54.207
Hmm.

14:54.680 --> 14:55.806
Never mind.

14:56.040 --> 14:58.725
Looks like I don't have to pretend I care.
(GRUNTS)

14:59.280 --> 15:00.327
(COCKS GUN)

15:08.400 --> 15:10.687
You have five seconds
to tell me exactly what's happening,

15:10.880 --> 15:12.291
or you're not leaving here alive.

15:20.520 --> 15:21.681
I'm sorry.

15:21.880 --> 15:23.644
Did I hurt your feelings by lying

15:23.840 --> 15:25.683
about my true intentions for being here?

15:25.880 --> 15:27.882
- Feels crappy, doesn't it?
- What did you do?

15:28.080 --> 15:29.889
I didn't do anything.
Damon on the other hand--

15:30.040 --> 15:31.087
-ls an idiot.
- Why?

15:31.280 --> 15:33.248
Because he's finally taking care
of the problem you couldn't?

15:33.440 --> 15:36.205
No. Because every time Rayna dies,
she comes back stronger.

15:36.400 --> 15:37.686
Except for that last one, right?

15:37.880 --> 15:40.042
She won't be stronger
when she's dead for good.

15:40.240 --> 15:41.480
Why do you even want her alive?

15:41.680 --> 15:44.490
You know, I wouldn't worry about that.
I'd worry about this.

15:47.800 --> 15:50.121
This is the spell those Shamans used
to create her.

15:50.560 --> 15:52.608
- And?
- Just read it.

15:57.120 --> 16:00.602
SHAMAN: Great Spirit, we call upon you
in this moment of need.

16:01.240 --> 16:02.810
They live on within you.

16:03.000 --> 16:05.480
BONNIE: The sword. It has linking magic.

16:06.080 --> 16:09.323
It creates a bond
between Rayna and her victims.

16:11.120 --> 16:12.201
We knew that.

16:12.360 --> 16:13.600
That's not all.

16:13.800 --> 16:15.882
The Shamans didn't want her
going to her eternal rest

16:16.120 --> 16:17.246
with any unfinished business.

16:17.440 --> 16:18.805
So they added an extra addendum.

16:21.920 --> 16:25.129
The scars are a fail-safe.

16:26.040 --> 16:30.807
If Rayna dies,
so does anyone she's marked.

16:32.560 --> 16:35.131
Stefan has one of those scars,
doesn't he?

16:39.040 --> 16:40.087
(RINGING)

16:42.520 --> 16:44.443
I'm not happy
about you going against my wishes.

16:44.640 --> 16:47.211
DAMON: But, I do suppose
that me lecturing anyone

16:47.440 --> 16:48.566
on respecting authority--

16:48.800 --> 16:50.245
Where's Rayna?

16:50.480 --> 16:51.527
In a moderately shallow grave.

16:51.680 --> 16:53.603
You know, I got tired of digging.
But it should do the trick.

16:53.800 --> 16:55.211
- You have to dig her up.
- No way.

16:55.440 --> 16:59.081
She'll flame to life underground,
suffocate, poof! Final life over.

16:59.280 --> 17:00.520
Huntress problem solved.

17:00.720 --> 17:02.643
Rayna can't die again.

17:04.000 --> 17:05.604
- Pardon me.
- The wounds from her sword.

17:05.800 --> 17:07.211
It's linked her to her victims.

17:07.400 --> 17:09.721
If Rayna dies one last time,

17:10.880 --> 17:12.369
so does Stefan.

17:15.680 --> 17:17.329
(GRUNTS)

17:21.000 --> 17:22.047
There you are.

17:23.319 --> 17:24.367
(SIGHS)

17:25.160 --> 17:26.525
What did she do to me?

17:27.079 --> 17:28.205
SCABBED WOMAN: Apologies.

17:29.000 --> 17:30.525
I haven't had visitors in years.

17:30.720 --> 17:32.768
And then all of a sudden
two in a matter of days.

17:33.040 --> 17:34.565
VALERIE: I spoke with her while you slept.

17:34.760 --> 17:36.091
Somebody beat us to the punch.

17:36.320 --> 17:37.367
Came in and took all the herbs.

17:38.400 --> 17:39.447
Well, we need more.

17:39.640 --> 17:41.005
SCABBED WOMAN: Unfortunately,
there is no more.

17:41.280 --> 17:42.884
That herb is rare for a reason.

17:43.240 --> 17:46.164
It has strong anti-magic,
and therefore anti-witch properties.

17:46.560 --> 17:49.166
Let's just say
this isn't from a bad laser peel.

17:49.360 --> 17:51.249
- There has to be more somewhere.
- There's not.

17:51.440 --> 17:54.046
Witches eradicated it from the world
a century ago.

17:55.120 --> 17:56.804
This was the only source.

17:57.680 --> 17:58.727
(SIGHS)

17:58.920 --> 18:00.968
DAMON: (ON VIDEO) I did have
a shockingly effective ally

18:01.160 --> 18:02.366
-tell me that you were here.
-(GU NSHOT)

18:03.000 --> 18:07.005
So, there are good vampires
and bad vampires.

18:07.200 --> 18:10.329
Yes. Kind of. It's complicated.

18:10.560 --> 18:12.688
And this is a bad vampire.

18:13.200 --> 18:15.202
- One that killed your sister?
- Yes.

18:15.440 --> 18:16.965
But that was a long time ago.

18:17.200 --> 18:18.850
And like I said, I'm not helping him.

18:19.040 --> 18:20.530
Again. It's complicated.

18:20.720 --> 18:22.802
Because you're helping his brother.

18:23.000 --> 18:25.207
- Who's a good vampire.
- Exactly.

18:26.200 --> 18:28.043
So this good vampire,

18:28.200 --> 18:30.043
does he feed on people, too?

18:32.200 --> 18:33.611
Does he kill them?

18:33.840 --> 18:35.330
Stefan...

18:36.520 --> 18:38.045
I mean, not right now, but--

18:38.280 --> 18:40.044
It's complicated?

18:42.040 --> 18:45.010
The thing is,
I've just spent the past few days with you

18:45.200 --> 18:47.168
learning about how much you hate vampires

18:47.360 --> 18:48.725
-and what they did to your town.
- I do.

18:48.880 --> 18:52.566
And yet, you just helped one of them
take down a vampire-killing machine.

18:54.200 --> 18:55.361
That doesn't sound complicated.

18:55.560 --> 18:59.042
Penny, you have no idea
what I've been through in this town.

18:59.320 --> 19:01.687
You're right. I don't.

19:02.000 --> 19:03.889
But I do wonder
how much of it you went through

19:04.160 --> 19:05.889
because you never took a real stand.

19:07.840 --> 19:09.729
At a certain point,

19:09.880 --> 19:13.407
it stops being the vampires' fault
that the town is like this.

19:14.480 --> 19:16.209
And it starts to be yours.

19:29.080 --> 19:30.241
Here we go.

19:30.720 --> 19:31.767
(GRUNTING)

19:34.000 --> 19:36.446
Come on. Where the hell are you?

19:38.760 --> 19:40.000
Come on.

19:43.600 --> 19:44.681
(CLINKS)

19:47.280 --> 19:49.123
(GRUNTS)
Please be alive.

20:01.800 --> 20:03.086
- Bottles are a go.
-(BABIES WAILING)

20:09.280 --> 20:12.602
Whoo. Diapers. Also a go.
Like, go away with them.

20:12.800 --> 20:14.768
- Oh, sorry.
-(CELL PHONE RINGING)

20:17.800 --> 20:19.086
- Hey.
- STEFAN: Hey.

20:19.320 --> 20:20.446
Is this a bad time?

20:20.640 --> 20:22.244
- I guess that's relative. (CHUCKLES)
-(BABIES WAILING)

20:22.440 --> 20:24.807
I mean, I'm not on the run
from a supernatural Huntress.

20:25.040 --> 20:27.441
- How are you?
- Oh, I've been better.

20:27.640 --> 20:29.927
Looks like it might actually be a while
before I can visit.

20:30.320 --> 20:32.482
Turns out those herbs
are a little more rare than we thought.

20:32.640 --> 20:33.721
Oh.

20:33.960 --> 20:36.645
Yeah. That's totally okay.

20:36.920 --> 20:40.083
Honestly, there's a chance there was
a little bit of contamination going on,

20:40.280 --> 20:42.851
so maybe it's not the worst thing.

20:46.840 --> 20:48.683
Hey listen, I was thinking, urn...

20:48.840 --> 20:51.081
I've been on the run with Valerie
for the last few days

20:51.280 --> 20:53.521
and without those herbs
I'm not gonna be able to slow down.

20:53.760 --> 20:55.842
But maybe you could tag in?

20:57.000 --> 20:59.367
I know being on the run seems awful.

20:59.600 --> 21:01.682
But it could be fun.
We could go to Europe.

21:01.840 --> 21:04.366
See the world. Just you and me.

21:06.840 --> 21:08.126
What do you think?

21:10.000 --> 21:11.365
Stefan...

21:12.840 --> 21:15.161
I just... I just want to see you, Care.

21:15.360 --> 21:17.442
Yeah, I want to see you, too, but...

21:17.640 --> 21:20.883
It's kind of a war zone over here
right now, and Alaric really--

21:21.040 --> 21:22.530
- He needs you.
- Mmm-hmm.

21:24.200 --> 21:25.964
Yeah, yeah, I get it.

21:26.720 --> 21:27.721
Uh...

21:28.360 --> 21:32.445
Well, we'll... We'll figure it out
once this Huntress thing is over.

21:32.680 --> 21:34.045
Yes. We will.

21:37.040 --> 21:39.646
(SIGHS) So, out of curiosity.

21:39.840 --> 21:42.650
What are your feelings about Dallas?

21:45.240 --> 21:46.401
Dallas, uh...

21:47.560 --> 21:49.324
I hadn't really thought about it.

21:49.520 --> 21:51.522
Well, it's not a terrible place to live.

21:52.080 --> 21:54.560
And, you know, the babies are here.

21:58.040 --> 22:00.486
RIC: Backup. I need backup right now.
And more diapers.

22:00.680 --> 22:02.250
CAROLINE: I'm sorry, Stefan. I got to run.

22:02.400 --> 22:03.481
Yeah. I get it.

22:04.920 --> 22:06.046
I love you.

22:07.360 --> 22:08.771
I love you, too.

22:11.920 --> 22:13.570
She's staying, isn't she?

22:16.320 --> 22:17.606
Looks like it.

22:19.760 --> 22:20.886
We'll figure something out.

22:23.440 --> 22:24.521
(GRUNTING)

22:25.440 --> 22:27.442
- Stefan. Hey.
-(CHOKING)

22:27.920 --> 22:29.604
What's wrong with me?

22:31.120 --> 22:32.531
(GASPING)
What's happening?

22:35.280 --> 22:36.930
Please be alive.

22:43.280 --> 22:44.361
- Stefan.
-(GASPS)

22:44.680 --> 22:45.806
My chest.

22:47.800 --> 22:48.801
(GASPS)

22:52.520 --> 22:53.646
Stefan?

22:54.800 --> 22:56.211
Stefan?

22:58.240 --> 22:59.765
Come on. Drink.

22:59.960 --> 23:01.610
No, damn it.

23:02.200 --> 23:03.247
(BLOWS)

23:06.960 --> 23:08.769
Stefan.

23:12.920 --> 23:15.890
Breathe. Come on, breathe. Breathe.
(GRUNTS)

23:19.880 --> 23:22.326
I can't stop it. It's not working.

23:23.320 --> 23:24.924
Breathe.

23:27.440 --> 23:28.965
Breathe!

23:29.160 --> 23:30.161
(GASPS)

23:44.680 --> 23:45.681
(PANTING)

23:46.680 --> 23:48.364
Thank God.

23:50.160 --> 23:51.207
(GRUNTS)

23:52.960 --> 23:54.007
(GROANS)

23:54.320 --> 23:55.367
Uh-oh.

24:02.320 --> 24:03.845
Uh-oh is right.

24:14.240 --> 24:15.321
What the hell are you doing?

24:15.520 --> 24:17.682
You said she gets stronger
each time she comes back to life.

24:17.880 --> 24:20.326
Damon can't kill her.
He is walking into a fight he can't win.

24:20.560 --> 24:22.210
The Armory is on their way
to Mystic Falls.

24:22.400 --> 24:24.004
- They'll be there soon.
- Not soon enough.

24:24.200 --> 24:25.247
She's connected to an Everlasting.

24:25.480 --> 24:27.005
Maybe I can weaken it. And her.

24:27.160 --> 24:28.844
And maybe that will kill her,
and Stefan too.

24:29.000 --> 24:31.731
If I do nothing, she'll kill Damon.

24:33.320 --> 24:34.481
You're willing to kill for him?

24:35.160 --> 24:37.288
Do you really think he cares
that much about you?

24:37.480 --> 24:38.925
Yeah. I do.

24:39.200 --> 24:41.567
You have no idea
what he's planning, do you?

24:42.880 --> 24:43.961
(DAMON PANTS)

24:44.920 --> 24:46.888
You wanna talk about Mr. Huntress now?

24:47.080 --> 24:49.651
Turns out I'm very interested
in this particular moment.

24:49.880 --> 24:51.564
- He was a vampire.
- Well, what do you know?

24:51.800 --> 24:54.121
Vampire-human affairs are my specialty.

24:54.320 --> 24:56.641
They were mine, too.
But they don't work out in the long run.

24:56.840 --> 24:58.285
Considering I staked him.

24:58.800 --> 24:59.847
Go ahead. Run.

25:00.040 --> 25:02.042
I don't mind chasing a second Salvatore.

25:02.240 --> 25:06.211
I couldn't maybe get like a
"I just saved your life" head start, huh?

25:06.440 --> 25:07.487
You better take it.

25:08.280 --> 25:09.770
On second thought...

25:13.000 --> 25:14.047
(GRUNTING)

25:16.720 --> 25:18.848
Don't say I never offered you anything.

25:19.880 --> 25:20.961
(GRUNTS)

25:21.160 --> 25:24.243
Well, if I could kill you,
this would be a much fairer fight.

25:24.440 --> 25:25.726
Your brother's dead no matter what.

25:25.960 --> 25:28.725
All you've done by saving my life
is gotten yourself killed.

25:29.920 --> 25:31.888
Don't worry. I don't miss.

25:34.440 --> 25:36.124
(GRUNTS SOFTLY)

25:37.400 --> 25:38.447
(GUNSHOTS)

25:44.520 --> 25:45.760
- Fire!
-(RAPID GUNSHOTS)

25:52.200 --> 25:53.486
Apparently neither do they.

26:02.480 --> 26:03.527
(FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING)

26:03.880 --> 26:05.166
Thanks.

26:05.760 --> 26:07.728
Rayna is officially in captivity.

26:10.360 --> 26:11.646
Where's the Bennett witch?

26:11.880 --> 26:13.609
Learning how little her friend
cares about her.

26:13.840 --> 26:15.968
I don't recall telling you to let her go.

26:16.160 --> 26:17.810
Well, I thought
we needed her help with Rayna.

26:18.000 --> 26:20.446
Yes. Rayna was the first priority.

26:21.240 --> 26:23.447
Bonnie Bennett is a close second.

26:27.520 --> 26:28.567
(DOOR OPENS)

26:30.960 --> 26:32.928
STEFAN: Looking for a bottle to celebrate?

26:33.720 --> 26:34.926
Gotta say, I'm impressed.

26:35.280 --> 26:36.361
I got your text.

26:36.760 --> 26:38.205
I didn't think you'd be able to kill her.

26:38.400 --> 26:41.244
Actually my exact message read,
"She's taken care of."

26:41.760 --> 26:43.649
- Yeah, she's taken care of.
- Yeah.

26:44.760 --> 26:45.886
What, so you didn't kill her?

26:46.120 --> 26:47.804
I did, a number of times.

26:48.040 --> 26:49.530
Turns out she only has eight lives.

26:50.920 --> 26:52.331
The last one's the problem.

26:53.040 --> 26:54.883
Turns out that if she dies for good,

26:55.080 --> 26:57.606
everyone with that scar
on your chest does as well.

27:01.480 --> 27:03.323
- So we can't kill her?
- No.

27:03.520 --> 27:05.010
But, the good news is,
the Armory has her,

27:05.200 --> 27:06.804
and they're not gonna let her escape.

27:07.000 --> 27:08.843
Right. Except for that time they did.

27:09.040 --> 27:11.247
Look, I know it's not ideal, okay?

27:12.720 --> 27:13.846
It's all we got.

27:14.160 --> 27:15.889
Caroline's staying in Dallas

27:17.400 --> 27:18.731
with Ric and the kids.

27:20.240 --> 27:21.765
I'm sorry to hear that, brother.

27:24.680 --> 27:26.125
I saw that coming.

27:27.360 --> 27:28.407
(SCOFFS)

27:29.080 --> 27:30.730
- You don't get it, do you?
- What?

27:30.960 --> 27:33.611
As long as I have this scar,
Rayna will hunt me.

27:34.360 --> 27:36.567
This isn't aboutjust you and me anymore.

27:36.800 --> 27:37.881
There's kids involved.

27:38.080 --> 27:39.206
I'm not gonna put them in danger.

27:39.400 --> 27:40.890
Which means that
I can't be with my girlfriend,

27:41.080 --> 27:42.411
as long as Rayna is alive.

27:42.600 --> 27:44.011
And you just told me she can never die.

27:44.200 --> 27:46.362
So, we have to figure out
another way to get rid of her.

27:46.600 --> 27:48.204
Or we need to get rid of this scar.

27:52.200 --> 27:53.804
That's a good plan.

28:00.040 --> 28:01.087
Foryou.

28:03.440 --> 28:04.487
STEFAN: What is this?

28:04.640 --> 28:07.769
We both know these last few months
have been impossible for me.

28:08.680 --> 28:12.765
I've been walking a tightrope.
And falling off, constantly.

28:14.200 --> 28:15.964
I'm not a good brother
when I'm not with Elena.

28:16.160 --> 28:18.447
And when I'm not a good brother,
people get hurt.

28:20.480 --> 28:21.891
So you're just gonna run away?

28:22.760 --> 28:24.649
Nope. I'm gonna stay at one place.

28:24.960 --> 28:27.042
Desiccated. Right next to her.

28:29.600 --> 28:30.806
Yeah.

28:32.120 --> 28:35.522
I saved your life. Time and time again.
I chose you.

28:35.720 --> 28:39.691
I sacrificed everyone
and everything for you.

28:41.120 --> 28:42.929
You're just gonna turn your back on me?
Now?

28:43.120 --> 28:45.521
We're vampires. It's temporary, Stefan.

28:47.680 --> 28:49.125
I'll see you again.

28:53.080 --> 28:54.286
Listen to me.

28:54.480 --> 28:57.609
If there is even a fraction of you
that cares about me,

28:58.160 --> 28:59.400
your brother,

29:00.040 --> 29:01.087
your family,

29:02.560 --> 29:05.086
then you will not walk out that door.

29:14.560 --> 29:17.325
Save a good bottle of that bourbon for me,
brother.

29:18.000 --> 29:20.810
We're gonna need it to sort all this out
in about 60 years.

29:25.520 --> 29:26.567
(DOOR OPENS)

29:26.880 --> 29:28.689
-(SIGHS)
-(DOOR CLOSES)

29:39.920 --> 29:40.967
(DOOR OPENS)

29:49.640 --> 29:51.369
Really not the best time, Matt.

29:51.840 --> 29:52.887
This won't take long.

29:53.040 --> 29:55.850
Look, I don't wanna have to kick you
out of here but I will.

29:56.200 --> 29:57.565
Yeah. I know you will.

29:57.800 --> 29:59.723
And there's nothing I can do to stop you.

30:01.200 --> 30:04.727
Because you're a vampire and I'm a human.

30:06.640 --> 30:08.722
I've been thinking
a lot about that lately.

30:09.760 --> 30:11.444
About my place in this town.

30:13.080 --> 30:14.411
My home.

30:16.560 --> 30:18.085
Whenever vampires are here,

30:18.840 --> 30:20.922
humans will always be at their mercy.

30:21.880 --> 30:24.087
Whatever laws we pass, you can break.

30:24.920 --> 30:27.321
Whatever lives we build, you can destroy.

30:28.200 --> 30:30.089
We don't stand a chance against you.

30:32.760 --> 30:34.125
That stops today.

30:36.360 --> 30:37.725
Excuse me?

30:41.760 --> 30:44.240
Vampires need to leave Mystic Falls.

30:44.920 --> 30:47.526
For good. All of you.

30:47.760 --> 30:48.807
(SCOFFS)

30:50.800 --> 30:53.770
Look, I appreciate whatever moral crisis
you're going through right now,

30:53.960 --> 30:56.042
but this is my home.

30:56.320 --> 30:57.890
I'm not going anywhere.

31:01.760 --> 31:03.842
This is footage from the Grill today.

31:04.040 --> 31:07.840
Of Damon doing
some very not-human things to Rayna.

31:08.120 --> 31:09.610
I've got footage of you, too.

31:11.120 --> 31:13.327
Hundreds of hours
from the town surveillance system.

31:13.960 --> 31:19.888
Now, I don't want to show it to anyone,
or expose you.

31:20.080 --> 31:21.650
Are you threatening me?

31:22.480 --> 31:24.801
Yeah. lam.

31:26.000 --> 31:27.570
And I hate that.

31:28.120 --> 31:31.203
I hate that I have to threaten my friend
because he's a vampire.

31:31.440 --> 31:33.363
I hate that
I'm friends with vampires at all.

31:33.560 --> 31:36.928
But this isn't about me. Or you.

31:39.320 --> 31:41.049
This is about our home.

31:41.800 --> 31:46.488
Which has been destroyed,
time and time again.

31:48.680 --> 31:51.001
This is the only way to break that cycle.

31:52.360 --> 31:54.328
You have until the end of the day.

31:59.320 --> 32:01.004
Damon, too.

32:02.600 --> 32:04.284
(DOOR OPENS AND CLOSES)

32:09.480 --> 32:11.130
(RATTLING)

32:53.480 --> 32:54.720
DAMON: Hey buddy.

32:55.920 --> 32:58.810
So, I know this is a crappy way
to do this, but,

32:59.000 --> 33:03.005
hey, I'm a crappy person,
so I guess it fits.

33:03.520 --> 33:06.808
By the time you read this,
I'll be desiccated in a coffin.

33:07.040 --> 33:08.087
Next to Elena.

33:08.240 --> 33:10.004
And I won't wake up until she does.

33:10.200 --> 33:14.250
So, I guess this might be
my official goodbye.

33:15.600 --> 33:19.605
I'm not gonna get lame or mushy,
but you deserve the truth.

33:20.600 --> 33:22.602
I'm telling Stefan
that the world is a better place

33:22.800 --> 33:24.564
without an Elena-less Damon.

33:25.240 --> 33:27.481
That it was best for everyone
that I was gone.

33:28.280 --> 33:29.884
I'm sure he'll see through that.

33:30.840 --> 33:34.242
Because to be completely honest,
I don't give a damn about the world.

33:35.320 --> 33:37.971
The truth is, I'm not in a good spot.

33:38.680 --> 33:40.284
Hell, I'm miserable.

33:40.480 --> 33:42.687
And I have been ever since she left me.

33:43.640 --> 33:47.201
Before her, I didn't know
what it was like to be happy.

33:48.880 --> 33:50.530
To be fulfilled.

33:51.600 --> 33:53.090
To be complete.

33:55.160 --> 33:56.810
But now I do.

33:58.160 --> 34:00.242
And now that I know that feeling...

34:00.920 --> 34:02.206
To live without it?

34:03.800 --> 34:05.848
(SCOFFS)
There's no point.

34:48.639 --> 34:50.210
So, that's it.

34:51.320 --> 34:52.685
Nice knowing you.

34:54.440 --> 34:56.168
BONNIE: You weren't even
gonna say goodbye.

35:01.560 --> 35:04.404
Enzo told me that you asked him
for Elena's coffin.

35:05.440 --> 35:08.330
He told me what you were planning.
I didn't believe him.

35:10.200 --> 35:11.326
I thought...
(SCOFFS)

35:11.520 --> 35:14.126
If Damon desiccates until Elena wakes up,

35:14.320 --> 35:15.731
I'll never see him again.

35:16.800 --> 35:17.847
(SIGHS)

35:18.320 --> 35:19.481
He'd never do that.

35:19.720 --> 35:22.326
Look, I wrote you a letter.
And I gave it to Stefan--

35:22.520 --> 35:23.601
Are we friends?

35:26.520 --> 35:27.567
(SCOFFS)

35:28.880 --> 35:29.927
Of course, Bonnie.

35:30.080 --> 35:32.321
We don't actively try
and kill each other anymore--

35:32.560 --> 35:34.244
No. I'm not doing that.

35:34.640 --> 35:37.530
- No insults. No jokes.
-(SIGHS)

35:41.520 --> 35:42.931
Are we friends?

35:45.080 --> 35:47.481
I know why you wanted to do this
in a letter.

35:49.400 --> 35:51.971
So you could desiccate in peace.

35:52.240 --> 35:54.925
Imagining whatever reaction you wanted.

35:55.560 --> 36:00.168
Me reading it and thinking,
"Huh, I'm really gonna miss him."

36:01.320 --> 36:02.685
Well, too bad.

36:03.240 --> 36:05.402
Because that's not my reaction.

36:07.080 --> 36:08.411
This is.

36:09.400 --> 36:12.609
I am not okay with this decision.

36:13.320 --> 36:15.926
I am not okay with you choosing yourself.

36:17.640 --> 36:20.849
And I am not okay with never seeing you,

36:23.760 --> 36:27.287
my best friend, ever again.

36:32.840 --> 36:34.285
This hurts me.

36:36.600 --> 36:37.601
(BONNIE SIGHS)

36:37.880 --> 36:39.450
(VOICE BREAKING) This hurts.

36:40.600 --> 36:42.284
This hurts me.
(SOBS)

36:43.440 --> 36:44.965
(BONNIE BREATHES DEEPLY)

36:48.640 --> 36:49.687
Hmm.

36:50.040 --> 36:51.530
And as you desiccate,

36:52.320 --> 36:54.800
and as you feel the pangs of hunger

36:55.120 --> 36:58.124
as the blood drains from your body,

36:59.320 --> 37:01.800
that's what I want you to remember.

37:04.120 --> 37:06.726
That you hurt me.
(SNIFFLES)

37:08.160 --> 37:09.400
Bon. Listen to me.

37:09.640 --> 37:11.802
No. No.

37:13.520 --> 37:15.488
You don't get to say goodbye.

38:41.640 --> 38:42.721
(COFFIN OPENS)

38:43.080 --> 38:45.242
STEFAN: Damon. Wake up.

38:46.080 --> 38:48.924
I need you. Wake the hell up!

38:49.080 --> 38:50.127
(GASPS)

38:51.240 --> 38:52.401
- We got to go.
- Why?

38:53.280 --> 38:54.327
(GUNSHOTS)

38:54.600 --> 38:55.601
(GRUNTS)

38:55.760 --> 38:58.001
She's back.
My scar opened up this morning.

38:58.240 --> 39:00.129
Rayna's not gonna stop until you're dead.

39:00.320 --> 39:02.641
Tyler, it's Stefan. My scar opened up.
I don't have much time.

39:02.840 --> 39:04.444
- I need you to warn Caroline.
- TYLER: Okay, I'm on it.

39:04.640 --> 39:05.926
But you should be running.

39:06.080 --> 39:07.127
I'm way ahead of ya.

39:07.360 --> 39:11.285
I never wanna hear the name
"Stefan Salvatore" ever again.

39:11.480 --> 39:12.527
(GROANS)

39:13.120 --> 39:14.281
BONNIE: How one stupid decision

39:14.480 --> 39:16.847
can turn your life into something
that you don't recognize.

39:17.120 --> 39:18.167
GROUP LEADER: Thank you, Bonnie.

39:20.440 --> 39:21.441
Damon.

39:21.600 --> 39:22.886
When was the last time
you talked to your fiancÃ©e?

39:23.120 --> 39:24.690
- What the hell do you want?
- Stefan's being hunted again

39:24.960 --> 39:25.961
and it's only a matter of time

39:26.120 --> 39:28.282
before Caroline is the bait
that's used to lure him out.

39:28.440 --> 39:29.805
My name is Caroline.

39:29.960 --> 39:33.123
I have an urgent message
for Stefan Salvatore.

39:33.280 --> 39:34.805
I'll be back before you know it.

39:36.280 --> 39:37.281
DAMON: Twenty-three minutes.

39:37.520 --> 39:38.646
Just enough time for me to get in,

39:38.800 --> 39:40.325
take out Little Miss Stabbypants
and grab Caroline.

39:40.560 --> 39:42.130
- Turn, turn, turn.
-(TIRES SCREECHING)

39:43.120 --> 39:44.167
We apologize for the interrupted program.

39:44.400 --> 39:46.004
- Well, that's not good.
-(GRUNTS)

39:46.320 --> 39:48.163
You've been poisoned with werewolf toxin.

39:48.640 --> 39:49.687
(GRUNTS)

39:49.960 --> 39:51.803
- MATT: Get up.
- You helping her?

39:52.800 --> 39:54.325
- MATT: All right, I did it. He's out.
{GROANS)

39:54.480 --> 39:56.164
STEFAN: Now I never see you again, right?

39:56.320 --> 39:57.481
Have a nice life.

40:00.560 --> 40:01.641
(GRUNTS)

40:01.800 --> 40:02.801
(EXHALES)

40:04.240 --> 40:05.321
(RAYNA SIGHS)

40:05.480 --> 40:09.246
I don't know about you...
(INHALES SHARPLY) But I'm exhausted.

40:10.320 --> 40:13.164
Feel like there should be champagne
or something.

40:13.560 --> 40:15.688
STEFAN: Yeah. You finally got me.

40:16.000 --> 40:17.161
Here I am.

40:18.000 --> 40:20.844
I'm totally not taking credit by the way.

40:22.160 --> 40:23.321
You came to me.

40:23.840 --> 40:26.889
You were safe. In the wind.

40:27.160 --> 40:28.730
You played it smart.

40:30.240 --> 40:32.242
Then you got dumb on me. What happened?

40:33.000 --> 40:35.367
I mean, okay, we know what happened.

40:35.520 --> 40:37.409
I took someone that you love.

40:38.560 --> 40:39.607
Damon.

40:40.040 --> 40:41.246
And Caroline.

40:41.760 --> 40:43.444
Guess that makes two people.

40:44.760 --> 40:48.128
Just out of curiosity,
which one of them brought you here?

40:48.520 --> 40:49.726
Her or him?

40:51.680 --> 40:53.603
Fine. Keep your secrets.

40:54.720 --> 40:57.200
You'll need something
to keep you company in hell.

41:05.280 --> 41:06.566
Or...

41:06.760 --> 41:08.444
There is a Plan B.

41:10.280 --> 41:12.965
But I know how you feel
about making choices.

41:13.440 --> 41:15.408
- Plan B?
- Yes.

41:15.760 --> 41:18.570
Because, believe it or not,
I don't actually want to kill you, Stefan.

41:18.720 --> 41:20.245
That doesn't make any sense.

41:20.720 --> 41:22.006
Just take my word for it.

41:22.240 --> 41:23.571
I know you don't deserve that mark.

41:23.720 --> 41:25.449
But somebody else does.

41:25.760 --> 41:28.240
What if I were to tell you
there was a way for me to transfer it

41:28.440 --> 41:30.442
to somebody a little bit more deserving?

41:32.480 --> 41:35.404
(CHUCKLES SOFTLY)
It should've been Damon all along.

41:35.560 --> 41:37.289
You know this as well as I do.

41:40.240 --> 41:42.288
You want to pit us against each other?

41:43.680 --> 41:44.966
Nice try.

41:47.600 --> 41:49.250
Except it wasn't her idea.

41:53.840 --> 41:55.285
It was mine.

42:28.640 --> 42:29.641
English - SDH
